Which feature on the ProLiant Gen9 servers allows a customer to protect the operating
system from malware by performing a verification of each component?
A. HP Smart Memory
B. RBSU Boot settings
C. RBSU Digitally Signed Program
D. UEFI Secure Boot

through the iLO?
A. HP Management Service
B. Agentless Management Service
C. Systems Insight Manager

A. list of filesystems currently mounted
B. operating system error logs
C. contact information for the system administrator
D. number and position of DIMMs installed
E. number of hard drives connected to an HP SmartArray controller

Which protocol defines accessing storage over Layer 2 Ethernet?
A. SAS
B. SCSIe
C. FCoE
D. iSCSI
Answer: D
What is Converged Networking?
A. The creation of a computing fabric consisting of interconnected nodes that look a fabric
when viewed collectively from a distance
B. A system that changes its structure, behavior, or resources according to demand
C. The ability to merge multiple data protocols (e.g. iSCSI. Fibre Channel, Ethernet) on the
same server I/Q interface
D. An approach to computer networking that allows network administrators to manage
network services through abstraction of lower level functionality
Answer: D
